      "date": "2012-07-13 14:47:26.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Verified\n\nTests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.2/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/439cf13c-ccf6-11e1-9a56-52540035b04c).  Ran 12 tests.  No failures.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "0a41c92e73cadb27aa6f432f27050f6c9905ee7e",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 234,
        "name": "Doug Oucharek",
        "email": "doug@cadentcomputing.com",
        "username": "Doug",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2012-07-18 04:28:11.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nThe Lustre repository is following coding guidelines similar to the Linux kernel (i.e. using tabs rather than spaces).  \n\nThere are a couple of git hooks referred to on the Using Gerrit page (http://wiki.whamcloud.com/display/PUB/Using+Gerrit) which checks over your patch to ensure it is following these guidelines.  Namely, they trigger the running of build/checkpatch.pl over the files.\n\nPlease install these hooks and fixed up added files to conform to the Lustre coding standard.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "ddf911a95b2ee71e96e1c7d40a4975a49c20f97b",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 6,
        "name": "Cory Spitz",
        "email": "cory.spitz@hpe.com",
        "username": "spitzcor"
      },
      "date": "2012-07-18 04:53:54.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nHi, Doug.  I see your point, but you've also taken a line/block at a time approach to avoid changing all lines at once.  We have a similar concern :)  See my LU-1419 comment dated 11/Jul/12 3:16 PM.  It's unfortunate that you may have missed that.  I should have reiterated the notice in the commit header.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
